        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:22PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 322 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 15 miles southwest of Roy to near
Variadero, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Variadero and Trementina.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 39 and 63.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
